D. S. Meyer
5.0 out of 5 stars All things a pencil should be.
Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2016
Pattern: Single ItemVerified Purchase
This pencil is fantastic. It has a barrel thicker than most mechanical pencils and is coated with a slightly shiny black paint. It's topped with a plastic piece (just because it's plastic doesn't mean it's of low quality) that holds the eraser and lead tube closed. Atop the black cap is a metal button with the Kaweco logo on top. Classy! It comes in a nice tin.
The mechanism inside is very solid feeling and makes a good audible click as the lead advances.
PROS:
Simple
Solid, but not heavy.
Minimal branding and logos-sleek!
Large barrel diameter makes it easy to hold.
CONS:
No pocket clip is included, though you can buy one if you feel it's necessary. I feel they only get in the way, but you should know it does not come with one.
The paint, while pretty, holds onto fingerprints easily. It doesn't effect performance at all, but I find myself wiping the pencil off a lot to keep it pretty.
5 stars! Any stationary fan will love it.
